               <msContents class="#MTM">
                  <summary><p>
  The bundle contains two works attributed to <persName xml:lang="ta">Auvaiyār</persName>:
  <list rend="numbered">
    <item>The <title xml:lang="ta">Ātticūṭi</title> (complete) (U1).</item>
    <item>the <title xml:lang="ta">Koṉṟaivēntāṉ</title> (complete) (U2).</item>
  </list>
</p>
<p>
  Both are named <foreign xml:lang="ta">Nīticcol</foreign> ("moral maxims") in the manuscript. These works are often used for learning the Tamil alphabet as the aphorisms are ordered alphabetically and represent all the letters of the Tamil alphabet. The bundle is possibly a school exercise. The lay-out of the page is in columns for the <foreign xml:lang="ta" rend="italic">mūlam</foreign>.
</p>
<p>
  There are several hands. The <title xml:lang="ta">Ātticūṭi</title> has been written by Aṅkappaṉ Piḷḷai (see U1b, f5r, c3, l1). The <title xml:lang="ta">Koṉṟaivēntāṉ</title> appears to have been written by Rāmacāmi Piḷḷai. Both names are fund on U3.</p>
   <p>Description based on the examination of the original manuscript (July 2020).</p> 
   <p>Dimensions after Cabaton (1912).</p>      
